jCobolLexer - A Cobol 85 X3.23-1985 lexer written in Java.

This directory contains source code, javadoc and final .jar of jCobolLexer.

Features:

1. Parse free, fixed and mixed sources.
2. Process continuation lines producing a single item (string, word, etc)
   as ouput.
3. Classify each token by semantic use (comment, separator, word, etc).
4. Select/Omit debug lines according run-time parameters.

Status:     Stable.

Pending:    Process COPY/REPLACE statements.

Documentation:

1. See javadoc documentation for general use.
2. See/use jUnit cases for testing.
3. Email me.

Libraries you will need:

1. Common-logging.
2. Log4j.

